Come join me on an adventure. The gastronomic experience I offer will take you to my ancestral origins. Every sip relives tradition, every hazy moments atests a lifetime of culture.

Lambanog is traditional Filipino distilled palm liquor made from coconut or nipa palm sap. It is derived from tubâ (palm toddy) that has been aged for at least 48 hours. It originates from Luzon island in the northern Philippines. It is commonly described as "coconut vodka" due to its clear to milky white color and high alcohol content.
